• Collaborate with other team members in preparing and executing performance testing;
• Assist the support team in activities related to application deployment where applicable;
• Participate in environment maintenance activities when QA services are required;
• Participate in knowledge sharing with other QA team members;
• Maintain up to date documentation and ensure that it is entered into appropriate repositories and systems of record;
• When applicable, evaluate, learn and implemented testing tools for manual, automated and performance testing;
• Learn IT technologies and products being implemented by DoITT and other agencies to develop efficient test approaches and participate in helping others to learn and use these approaches.

Minimum Qual Requirements:
1. A baccalaureate degree in computer science, engineering or a related field from an accredited college and four years of satisfactory full-time experience related to IT automation engineering, monitoring engineering, management of infrastructure; or

2. Eight years of satisfactory full-time experience related to IT automation engineering, monitoring engineering, management of infrastructure;

3. Education and/or experience which is equivalent to "1" or "2" above.

Preferred Skills:
The preferred candidate should possess the following:
• Minimum 8 years in developing, implementing and executing automated test scripts for business applications with browser-based UI;
• Hands on experience with current state of Selenium WebDriver open source test automation framework and techniques, experience with Java based frameworks is preferred;
• Experience with other test automation tools HP/Micro Focus UFT, Cucumber is preferred;
• Experience and knowledge of automation test technologies applicable to mobile devices like Appium is a plus;
• Prior software development experience, preferably with an object oriented programming or scripting language, Java/JavaScript/Python/C#  are plus
• Experience in managing SDLC process and test execution with one or all of the following systems, preferred: Azure DevOps (formerly TFS or VSTS), ALM Quality Center;
• Experience with integrating automated tests into DevOps environment based on Azure DevOps (TFS, VSTS), Jenkins, or TeamCity is a plus
• Experience in functional testing of applications with browser-based UI;
• Understanding HTML specifics needed for test automation;
• Experience in manual and automated testing of webservices/APIs using SOAP and REST protocols with appropriate tools like PostMan and Soap UI or similar;
• Experience in handling various file formats as source of test data and as means of configuration, including but not limited to Java property files, CSV, XML, JSON, Excel;
• Understanding multi-tier application architecture;
• Understanding the concept of relational databases, experience in using SQL query language to build and use queries for testing and data preparation purposes; 
• Understanding of the purpose and scope of performance testing process and tools;
• Interest and ability to learn new technologies and tools, and acquire new skills;
• Proficient computer user with experience using standard productivity tools including Microsoft Project, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Visio for document development and data preparation and handling;
• Ability to take strategic direction from executive management and participate in strategic planning activities throughout the lifetime of the project;
• Ability to see tasks through to completion without significant guidance;
• Strong issue resolution and investigation skills;
• Ability to articulate and document the steps taken to resolve an issue;
• Ability to take initiative, be a decisive and show confidence in decisions made;
• Ability to see the big picture/system understanding with capability/potential to dive into low level details to support problem isolation;
• Strong oral and written communication skills and the ability to clearly articulate to all project members and stakeholders;
• Strong “soft skills” needed to influence stakeholders and successfully collaborate with others;
• Team player who works well with technical and non-technical resources;
• Flexibility to work overtime as required (may need to be on call to support deployments or production validation activities during peak times).

Job Description:
DoITT provides for the sustained, efficient and effective delivery of IT services, infrastructure and telecommunications to enhance service delivery to New York City's residents, businesses, employees and visitors. As the City's technology leader, DoITT is responsible for maintaining the foundational IT infrastructure and systems that touch every aspect of City life from public safety to human services, from education to economic development crossing the full spectrum of governmental operations.

The successful candidate will serve as a Database Architect reporting to the Infrastructure Management Division. The Database Architect’s role is to plan, design, and analyze the agency’s Database and Storage infrastructure according to best practices, while ensuring high levels of data quality and availability. This individual will also be integral in the development, implementation of policies and procedures to ensure consistent storage provisioning, uptime, and regulatory compliance. This is to ensure the integrity and availability of databases and their accompanying software. This position will also be responsible for overall capacity planning, backup and restore process design, performance analysis, and developing data disaster recovery plans. Additional responsibilities include:
• Plan, design, and analyze the agency’s Database and Storage infrastructure according to best practices, while ensuring high levels of data quality and availability;
• Integral in the development, implementation of policies and procedures to ensure consistent storage provisioning, uptime, and regulatory compliance;
• Ensure the integrity and availability of databases and their accompanying software;
• Overall capacity planning, backup and restore process design, performance analysis, and developing data disaster recovery plans;
• Develop and establish technical and operations, installation, preventative maintenance and overall system performance standards;
• Provide architectural expertise, direction, and assistance to database administrators and Engineering teams;
• Design, architect, Install and configure relevant network components to ensure Enterprise database infrastructure as well as database consistency and integrity;
• Conduct research and make recommendations on database products, services, protocols, and standards in support of procurement and development efforts;
• Establish appropriate end-user database access control levels;
• Design redundant systems and policies for disaster recovery and archiving to ensure effective protection and integrity of storage appliances and stored data assets.
• As a member of strategic design for the City, assist in the development of policies and standards for technology initiatives;
• Interact with agencies and internal department heads to determine needs to fulfill executive management project plans/priorities;
• Maintain current knowledge of storage-related laws, trends, and issues, including current and emerging technologies and best practices. Develop strategies and policies to ensure best-practice based regulatory compliance and reduce the enterprise’s legal exposure.
• Perform capacity planning analysis and other needs assessments to inform storage architecture strategy.
• Project management/project lifecycle experience.
• Perform special projects and initiatives as assigned.

Preferred Skills:
The preferred candidate should possess the following:
• Excellent knowledge on database transaction, performance tuning and security audits;
• Excellent knowledge of SAN, NAS, RAID, SCSI, Fibre Channel, tape, clustering, encryption, content-addressable storage, technologies from EMC, Netapp and Pure solutions;
• In-depth knowledge Multiple Database architectures (Oracle, MS SQL);
• Advanced skill, documentation and overall windows 2008/2012/2016 OS;
• Advanced skill, documentation and multiple in RHEL OS versions;
• Experience working with Multiple Storage Solutions (EMC- PorwerMax, Xtremio, VMAX, Netapp/Storagegrid, Pure   X70, X90);
• Knowledge of Cloud solutions (AWS and MS Azure);
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills;  
• Excellent analytic, organization, presentation, customer service and facilitation skills;  
• Excellent problem-solving skills;
• Ability to handle multiple tasks under tight deadlines.

Job Description:
About New York City Cyber Command (NYC3)
Mission. NYC Cyber Command leads the City’s cyber defense efforts, working across more than 100 agencies and offices to prevent, detect, respond, and recover from cyber threats. NYC3 protects NYC infrastructure and critical systems from malicious attacks and safeguards the data, devices, and services of the City.

Culture. Foremost, we serve the people of the City of New York, so earning - and keeping - their trust is paramount. To deserve that trust, we relentlessly focus on facts, provide sound judgment, and maintain a healthy culture. We pride ourselves on having a respectful and inclusive workplace built on kindness, honest intellectual debate, and excellent work.

About the Job
The Senior Audit Manager will serve as the deputy lead for the Audit and Compliance unit for NYC3. Under the supervision of the Director of Audit and Compliance, the Senior Audit Manager will help to shape the Audit and Compliance program and enforce policies and procedures with regards to cyber security audits of and compliance of the NY City Agencies.

Responsibilities include:- Conduct evaluations of cybersecurity programs or their individual components to determine compliance with Citywide and NYC3 published cybersecurity policies and standards;
- Review and conduct audits of the NYC Agencies cybersecurity programs and projects;
- Staff, manage, and mentor team members;
- Assess and revise NYC Agencies’ documented information security and technology policies, procedures and practices;
- Develop and manage internal policies, procedures and processes as related to compliance and best practices;
- Provide recommendations for possible improvements to the Audit and Compliance program;
- Review service performance reports identifying any significant issues and variances, initiating, where necessary, corrective actions and ensuring that all outstanding issues are followed up on and remediated;
- Ensure that cybersecurity requirements are properly included in contract language and delivered timely;
- Draft and present audit findings report accompanied with working papers, concise controls assessment and systems testing reports (both narrative and table based).

Preferred Skills:
The preferred candidate should possess the following:
-       BS/BA degree in Business, Management Information Systems, Law, Computer Science, or related field;
- JD, LLM, Master of Business Administration, Master of Public Administration or similar;
- A minimum of 6-8 years of experience auditing IT systems;
- One or more of the following ISACA certifications is required:
- Certified Information Systems Auditor (CISA)
- Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)
- Certified in Risk and Information Systems Control (CRISC)
- Certified Information Security Manager (CISM)
- 6+ years of relevant forensic and/or cyber security related experience;
- 6+ years’ experience in operational IT and audit/consulting, specifically performing penetration testing and vulnerability assessment engagements;
