Job Description:
DoITT provides for the sustained, efficient and effective delivery of IT services, infrastructure and telecommunications to enhance service delivery to New York City's residents, businesses, employees and visitors. As the City's technology leader, DoITT is responsible for maintaining the foundational IT infrastructure and systems that touch every aspect of City life from public safety to human services, from education to economic development crossing the full spectrum of governmental operations.

This position is in alignment with the City’s strategy to create a program at DoITT that will effectively serve as the City’s consulting arm in addressing agencies’ technology needs. This position will leverage DoITT’s expertise to deliver high quality solutions that meet agency business needs. Each City agency has different business needs, providing many opportunities for interesting work but also presenting dynamic challenges to the resources deployed by DoITT.

The successful candidate will serve as an IT Architect reporting to the Enterprise and Solution Architecture Division.
Responsibilities will include:
• Participate in the planning and design of the IT capabilities within DoITT and across the enterprise in order to meet desired business objectives;
• Develop the framework and tools for delivering technical solutions which meet mission critical business objectives;
• Coach and mentor architectural and development resources on complex Citywide projects;
• Directly engage and provide architectural leadership with business and technical partners from various City agencies;
• Participate in the Request for Proposal (RFP) of projects and assist in formulating the technical solution blueprints, architecture and effort estimates;
• Plan and design the security, application, information, UX, integration, cloud, and infrastructure architectures that ensure the delivery of a stable, scalable system with capabilities aligned to customer requirements;
• Help define and document how the components of the business application relate to each other, including how shared technology services and capabilities will best support the client business objectives;
• Work in collaboration with other City architects, conduct research and advise project management on appropriate products, city and industry-wide technology capabilities and standards to address system needs and improve efficiency;
• Partner with project teams and business owners to obtain buy-in for application and technology architecture decisions;
• Assist agencies in leveraging standards and best practices;
• Work conjunction with the other Enterprise and Solution Architecture Division architects, make recommendations on aligning solutions to City and agency strategic roadmaps;
• Work with development teams to assure alignment of technology architecture work products within the proposed solution architecture;
• Produce appropriate project deliverables as required, e.g. Vision, Solution Architecture, Interface Design/Strategy, Workflow Design/Strategy, Application Security Design/Strategy;
• Assist in developing enterprise reference architectures and development standards;
• Address client concerns and escalate all project issues appropriately and manage them to resolution;
• Transition all project artifacts and knowledge to agency staff prior to disengaging from a project.

Preferred Skills:
We are looking for candidates who not only have the required experience and skills but can demonstrate a level of professionalism and customer service we expect from top-tier consultants in the private sector. If you are an IT professional who combines high business acumen with technical expertise and team collaboration, you are strongly encouraged to apply.

The preferred candidate should possess the following:
• 2+ years of experience architecting complex large scale systems incorporating packaged and custom applications;
• A minimum of 5 years of experience in building enterprise and scalable web applications using J2EE/.NET/Python/PHP and various integration technologies;
• Experience in architecting leading Customer Relationship Management Systems
• Strong understanding of client/server architecture in on-premise, SaaS, PaaS and IaaS Architectures;
• Must be passionate and enthusiastic about modern technologies, industry trends and new opportunities;
• Must will be willing to lead and be hands-on during POCs;
• Strong knowledge and experience across business, security, application, information, integration, UX and infrastructure architecture domains;
• Strong knowledge of project management, multi-tier applications, internet, intranet, and mobile applications, release methodologies, technical support, and production support;
• Strong knowledge of Security Architecture and its standards and patterns (SAML, OAuth, Role Based Accesses Control (RBAC), Attribute Based Access Controls (ABAC), Federation, etc.);
• Strong knowledge of operating systems (Linux, Windows, etc), database platforms (Oracle, Microsoft, IBM, etc), desktop, mobile, and web platforms and application frameworks (Java, .NET, etc), content managers, portal products, application integration, SOA, cloud, development methodologies and environments;
• Demonstrated experience working with all levels of customers; technical and non-technical staff; outstanding collaboration and team building skills;
• Strong knowledge of search technologies such as Google Search Appliance, Elastic Search and Solr;
